1. *Pametni* ljudi su uvijek spremni na učenje novih stvari. (Smart people are always ready to learn new things.)
2. Oni su među *pametnijim* studentima na fakultetu. (They are among the smarter students at the university.)
3. *Pametna* odluka bi bila da krenemo ranije kako ne bismo kasnili. (A smart decision would be to start earlier so we don't be late.)
4. Oni su *pametno* uložili novac u dionice i ostvarili značajnu dobit. (They invested their money smartly in stocks and made significant profits.)
5. Da bi bio *pametan*, treba slušati druge ljude i prihvatati njihove ideje. (To be smart, you need to listen to other people and accept their ideas.)
6. *Pametno* bi bilo da iskoristimo priliku dok je još imamo. (It would be smart to take advantage of the opportunity while we still have it.)
7. Ona je vrlo *pametna* žena i ima uspješnu karijeru. (She is a very smart woman and has a successful career.)
8. Možda bi bilo *pametnije* da pričekamo i donesemo odluku nakon što prikupimo sve informacije. (Maybe it would be smarter to wait and make a decision after we gather all the information.)
9. *Pametni* telefoni su postali neizostavan dio našeg života. (Smartphones have become an indispensable part of our lives.)
10. Nije dovoljno biti samo *pametan*, treba biti i marljiv i uporan. (It's not enough to be just smart, you also need to be hardworking and persistent.)